`debounce` function is not available out of the box. If you donot want to add a separate package, you can implement your own debounce function as below

```
const debounce = (fn, time) =&gt; {
  let timeout;

  return function() {
    const functionCall = () =&gt; fn.apply(this, arguments);
    
    clearTimeout(timeout);
    timeout = setTimeout(functionCall, time);
  }
}
```

For full reference please check [Medium][1]


  [1]: https://medium.com/@TCAS3/debounce-deep-dive-javascript-es6-e6f8d983b7a1

